          "body": "When the Spirit of the LORD comes upon Jahaziel the Levite (20:14), the divine response is structurally identical to the Exodus oracle. 'Do not fear or be dismayed' (20:15, 17) echoes Exodus 14:13-14; 'you need not fight in this battle; station yourselves and stand and see the salvation of the LORD' is an almost verbatim parallel to Moses at the Red Sea ('Stand still and see the salvation of the LORD — the LORD will fight for you, and you shall keep silent,' Exodus 14:13-14). The Chronicler is not quoting accidentally; he is claiming that Jehoshaphat's crisis is the Exodus event re-enacted in the Judean wilderness. The same God who parted the sea is now setting ambushes in the Dead Sea desert. Jahaziel's five-generation Levitical genealogy (20:14) anchors the oracle in the worshipping community — the word of the LORD in this chapter comes not through a prophet-outsider but through the congregation's own singers."
